"{\"abstract\":\"Topic modeling based on latent Dirichlet allocation (LDA) has been a framework of choice to deal with multimodal data, such as in image annotation tasks. Recently, a new type of topic model called the Document Neural Autoregressive Distribution Estimator (DocNADE) was proposed and demonstrated state-of-the-art performance for text document modeling. In this work, we show how to successfully apply and extend this model to multimodal data, such as simultaneous image classification and annotation. Specifically, we propose SupDocNADE, a supervised extension of DocNADE, that increases the discriminative power of the hidden topic features by incorporating label information into the training objective of the model and show how to employ SupDocNADE to learn a joint representation from image visual words, annotation words and class label information. We also describe how to leverage information about the spatial position of the visual words for SupDocNADE to achieve better performance in a simple, yet effective manner. We test our model on the LabelMe and UIUC-Sports datasets and show that it compares favorably to other topic models such as the supervised variant of LDA and a Spatial Matching Pyramid (SPM) approach.\",\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"47833747\",\"name\":\"Y. Zheng\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/47833747\"},{\"authorId\":\"34853917\",\"name\":\"Y. Zhang\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/34853917\"},{\"authorId\":\"1777528\",\"name\":\"H. Larochelle\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/1777528\"}],\"citationVelocity\":8,\"citations\":[{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"2256606\",\"name\":\"Meixiang Xu\"},{\"authorId\":\"1749780\",\"name\":\"Zhenfeng Zhu\"},{\"authorId\":\"38161033\",\"name\":\"Y. Zhao\"}],\"doi\":\"10.1007/s11042-018-6578-0\",\"intent\":[\"background\"],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"33bda213520d4c1b5e6cadd0954cb4956d9fa343\",\"title\":\"Towards learning a semantic-consistent subspace for cross-modal retrieval\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/33bda213520d4c1b5e6cadd0954cb4956d9fa343\",\"venue\":\"Multimedia Tools and Applications\",\"year\":2018},{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"4492316\",\"name\":\"Fangyi Zhu\"},{\"authorId\":\"1755773\",\"name\":\"Zhanyu Ma\"},{\"authorId\":\"1876419\",\"name\":\"X. Li\"},{\"authorId\":\"145082678\",\"name\":\"G. Chen\"},{\"authorId\":\"1699469\",\"name\":\"Jen-Tzung Chien\"},{\"authorId\":\"1891766\",\"name\":\"Jing-Hao Xue\"},{\"authorId\":\"145505204\",\"name\":\"J. Guo\"}],\"doi\":\"10.1016/j.neucom.2018.02.099\",\"intent\":[],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"65c33cc3555d80669767f0e0a16f2eb85e583628\",\"title\":\"Image-text dual neural network with decision strategy for small-sample image classification\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/65c33cc3555d80669767f0e0a16f2eb85e583628\",\"venue\":\"Neurocomputing\",\"year\":2019},{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"71281032\",\"name\":\"F. Wang\"},{\"authorId\":\"46700405\",\"name\":\"J. Liu\"},{\"authorId\":\"7671172\",\"name\":\"S. Zhang\"},{\"authorId\":\"2835545\",\"name\":\"G. Zhang\"},{\"authorId\":\"49345810\",\"name\":\"Y. Zheng\"},{\"authorId\":\"50080170\",\"name\":\"X. Li\"}],\"doi\":\"10.1109/PIC.2018.8706284\",\"intent\":[\"methodology\"],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"96f923de17f2a6b928671ae97aa5e71ab3454dd3\",\"title\":\"Image Annotation through Adaptive Dependency Fusion\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/96f923de17f2a6b928671ae97aa5e71ab3454dd3\",\"venue\":\"2018 IEEE International Conference on Progress in Informatics and Computing (PIC)\",\"year\":2018},{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"1414039209\",\"name\":\"Lakhdar Laib\"},{\"authorId\":\"1698715\",\"name\":\"Mohand Sa\\u00efd Allili\"},{\"authorId\":\"1402156778\",\"name\":\"S. Ait-Aoudia\"}],\"doi\":\"10.1016/J.IMAGE.2019.05.012\",\"intent\":[\"background